{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "# Q: Bug: write_file fails in Plan Mode when session ID is missing from path\n**Source:** https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/issues/23696\n\n## The Problem / Request\n### What happened?\nThe policy regex for `write_file` and `replace` tools in Plan Mode was too restrictive. It required exactly two subdirectories under `.gemini/tmp/` (e.g., `[user-hash]/[session-id]`) before reaching the `plans/` directory. This caused file writing in Plan Mode to fail in environments or test cases where the session ID was not present in the path.\n\n### What did you expect to happen?\n`write_file` should succeed in Plan Mode as long as the file is written to the `plans/` directory under `.gemini/tmp/`, regardless of whether an intermediate session ID directory is present.\n\n### Client information\nN/A - This was a policy configuration issue in the codebase.\n\n### Login information\nN/A\n\n### Additional context\nFixed in PR #23695.\n\n## The Solution / Discussion\n### Response 1\nFound possible duplicate issues:\n\n- #21359\n\nIf you believe this is not a duplicate, please remove the `status/possible-duplicate` label.\n<!-- gemini-cli-deduplication -->\n\n", "timestamp": null, "embedding": [0.9806145429611206, 0.21656230092048645, -2.928631544113159, -1.5727814435958862, 1.142787218093872, -1.574117660522461, 0.5388274788856506, -0.03524177148938179, -0.9264335036277771, -1.519116997718811, -0.4064823091030121, 0.6121878027915955, 0.4527341425418854, -0.20317718386650085, 0.31877583265304565, -0.6111154556274414, 0.40475592017173767, -0.7685421705245972, -0.16574595868587494, 0.7237668037414551, -0.6408572793006897, -1.2406193017959595, 0.08019323647022247, 0.34755054116249084, 2.246896982192993, 0.7394512891769409, 0.5135604739189148, 0.06508486717939377, -0.7008382081985474, 0.062273602932691574, 2.2024550437927246, -0.9502481818199158, -0.12274932861328125, 0.009135589003562927, -1.168589472770691, -1